==English==
===Pronunciation===
*stēl, /stiːl/, /sti:l/
*{{audio|en-us-steal.ogg|Audio (US)}}

====Homophones====
*[[steel]]

===Transitive verb===
'''to steal''' ([[stole]], [[stolen]])

# to [[take]] something from somebody against their will
# to [[move]], [[carry]], or [[place]] surreptitiously
# to [[get]] or effect surreptitiously or artfully
# to draw attention unexpectedly in (an entertainment), especially by being the outstanding performer
# to [[copy]] something without permission (''He stole my credit card number.'')
#{{Baseball}}  to [[advance]] safely to (another base) during the delivery of a pitch, without the aid of a base hit, walk, passed ball, or wild pitch
#to [[move]] [[silent]]ly or [[secret]]ly
#:''He '''stole''' across the room, trying not to wake her.''

====Synonyms====
* {{AU}} {{slang}} [[flog]]
* [[half-inch]] (''Cockney rhyming slang'')
* {{slang}}: [[knock off]], [[lift]], [[nick]], [[pinch]], [[pocket]]
*[[rob]]
*[[thieve]]

====Related terms====
*[[shoplift]]
*[[steal away]]

